 Native reds have been wiped out in the north of England , the Isle of Wight and Scotland after rival grey squirrels arrived from America in the 19th century .
Numbers of the reds , have been dwindling thanks in large part to the squirrel pox virus carried by greys .
Experts say a lack of habitats caused them to disappear from the area .
Experts think endangered red squirrels have achieved immunity to the killer pox carried by their grey rivals .